       <button onclick="returnToGraph()">graph</button>
       <h6>Example Input:</h6>
       <p><strong>Valid:</strong><br/>Rect: y = 2x+sin(x)^3<br/>Polar: r = sin(4t)/2 //(use t for &#x03b8)<br/>Para: y = 4sin(2t) x = 4cos(t) </p>
       <p>With update 3.0 implicit multiplication and the 'a^b' syntax for exponentiation are now valid.</p>
       <p><strong>To clear graph:</strong> set x and y limits and leave y= blank.</p>
       <ul>
          <lh><strong>Available Functions &nbsp; &amp; &nbsp; Constants</strong></lh> 
          <li>arccos()</li>
          <li>arcsin()</li>
          <li>arctan()</li>
          <li>cos()</li>
          <li>sin()</li>
          <li>tan()</li>
          <li>pow(n,m) //n raised to the power m (n^m)</li>
          <li>exp()    //e raised to power n exp(n)</li>
          <li>abs()</li>
          <li>log() </li><!--consider changing to ln() and building your own log function-->
          <li>sqrt()</li>
          <li>E or e = 2.72...</li>
          <li>PI or pi = 3.14...</li>
       </ul>

